# changelog for reddo

version 0.1.5 (2 Jun 2005):
 * systran support
 * bug fixes

version 0.1.4 (28 May 2005):
 * list supported langpairs for each server (--list-langpairs)
 * pikachu server
   (http://pikachize.eye-of-newt.com/)

version 0.1.3 (25 May 2005):
 * random server and list servers bug fix, sorry about that.
   (thanks RuNGaX <rungax (at) gmail (dot) com>)

version 0.1.2 (24 May 2005):
 * list supported servers (--list-servers)
 * special random server (-s random, --server=random)
 * verbose mode (-v, --verbose)

version 0.1.1 (17 May 2005):
 * Man page updated
 * RPM package using distutils
 * Reddo library is now installed in /usr/share/reddo/reddolib 
   instead of python site-packages. This directory is added to
   sys.path at the program startup
 * Debian packages improvements
 * Improved behaviour behind anormal server answers

version 0.1 (11 May 2005):
 * Initial Release
 * Python distutils install
 * Debian packages
 * Manual page
 * Google and Babelfish servers support

